# Runbook core-layer implementation spec (Phase 1)

Approved-plan companion. Line refs verified against HEAD 788a69c9. The `model` package lives at repo root `model/` (NOT internal/model). Reconciled decisions: step result statuses are **done|failed|skipped** (constants `StepDone`, `StepFailed`, `StepSkipped`); Comments IN; Commits/Attachments/Anchors OUT; no `SetRunTask`.

## 0. Design summary

- New entity kind `runbook` at `refs/cc-notes/runbooks/<id>`, cloned structurally from the sprint/project template (commit 0fcfa78b), plus two new mechanisms: **positioned steps** (criteria template + explicit position) and **embedded runs** (log-entry stamping + criteria-style keyed mutation, one level deeper).
- Position encoding: lexicographic fractional-index string over base-36 (§2).
- Runbook joins the fold disk cache (§5.5) — and while in cache.go, close the pre-existing sprint/project cache gap (stewardship).
- 10 new ops; generic `SetTitle`/`SetDescription`/`AddLabel`/`RemoveLabel`/`AddComment` reused verbatim.

## 1. Types — `model/model.go`

