### 5.6 Dedupe — `internal/store/dedupe.go`
- `findDuplicate` (:33-129): `case "runbook":` fold candidate via `fold.Runbook`, `ListRunbooks`, match live only (`rb.ArchivedAt == 0` — an archived twin never suppresses re-creating the procedure) via `sameRunbookContent`.
- `dedupeCovered` (:142-157): add `model.CreateRunbook, model.AddStep` ONLY (never run ops — a pack bundling StartRun skips dedupe so no run record can be silently dropped; same reasoning as AppendEntry). Extend its doc comment.
- Comparators (mirror `sameCriteria` :198-205 — compare content in folded order, ignore nonce IDs and position encoding, else two clients computing different midpoints for the same list defeat dedupe):

```go
func sameRunbookContent(a, b model.Runbook) bool {
	return a.Title == b.Title &&
		a.Description == b.Description &&
		slices.Equal(a.Labels, b.Labels) &&
		sameSteps(a.Steps, b.Steps)
}

// sameSteps compares steps by content — text and command, in folded (position)
// order — ignoring the per-step nonce id and the position encoding itself.
func sameSteps(a, b []model.RunbookStep) bool {
	return slices.EqualFunc(a, b, func(x, y model.RunbookStep) bool {
		return x.Text == y.Text && x.Command == y.Command
	})
}
```

